      • KEY_AUDIO_FOCUS_NAVIGATION_REJECTED_DURING_CALL

        public static final java.lang.String KEY_AUDIO_FOCUS_NAVIGATION_REJECTED_DURING_CALL
        Key to indicate whether audio focus requests for android.hardware.automotive.audiocontrol.V1_0.ContextNumber.NAVIGATION should be rejected if focus is currently held by android.hardware.automotive.audiocontrol.V1_0.ContextNumber.CALL.

        The value is a boolean (1 or 0) where:

        • 1 indicates NAVIGATION should be rejected when a CALL is in progress.
        • 0 indicates NAVIGATION and CALL should be allowed to hold focus concurrently.

        Recommended false as default value.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • KEY_AUDIO_PERSIST_VOLUME_GROUP_MUTE_STATES

        public static final java.lang.String KEY_AUDIO_PERSIST_VOLUME_GROUP_MUTE_STATES
        Key to indicate if mute state should be persisted across boot cycles.

        The value is a boolean (1 or 0) where:

        • 1 indicates volume group mute states should be persisted across boot cycles.
        • 0 indicates volume group mute states should not be persisted across boot cycles.

      • KEY_PACKAGES_DISABLED_ON_RESOURCE_OVERUSE

        public static final java.lang.String KEY_PACKAGES_DISABLED_ON_RESOURCE_OVERUSE
        Key for a ; separated list of packages disabled on resource overuse.

        The value is written by com.android.car.watchdog.CarWatchdogService.

        The value is read by user interfaces (such as launcher) that show applications disabled on resource overuse. When a user selects any application from this list, the user interface should either enable the application immediately or provide user affordance to enable the application when the driving conditions are safe.

        When an application (which is on this list) is enabled, CarService will immediately remove the application's package name form the list.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • KEY_USER_TOS_ACCEPTED

        public static final java.lang.String KEY_USER_TOS_ACCEPTED
        Key for an int value to indicate whether the user has accepted the Terms of Service.

        The value is an int value where:

        • 0 - the acceptance value is unknown. In this case, functionality should not be restricted.
        • 1 - the acceptance value is false. In this case, some system functionality is restricted.
        • 2 - the acceptance value is true. In this case, system functionality is not restricted.

        Recommended 0 as default value.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • KEY_UNACCEPTED_TOS_DISABLED_APPS

        public static final java.lang.String KEY_UNACCEPTED_TOS_DISABLED_APPS
        Key for a string value to indicate which apps are disabled because the user has not accepted the Terms of Service.

        The value is a string value of comma-separated package names. For example, "com.company.maps,com.company.voiceassistant,com.company.appstore"

        Recommended "" as default value.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • VISIBLE_USER_ALLOCATION_PER_ZONE

        public static final java.lang.String VISIBLE_USER_ALLOCATION_PER_ZONE
        Defines non-current visible users to assign per each occupant zone.

        For the format of the value, check Global#VISIBLE_USER_ALLOCATION_PER_ZONE. This is per user setting and system will apply this when this user is the current user during the boot up.

        If both Global#VISIBLE_USER_ALLOCATION_PER_ZONE and this value is set, this value will be used and Global#VISIBLE_USER_ALLOCATION_PER_ZONE will be ignored.

        另请参阅:
        常量字段值

      • KEY_DRIVER_ALLOWED_TO_CONTROL_MEDIA

        public static final java.lang.String KEY_DRIVER_ALLOWED_TO_CONTROL_MEDIA
        Key to indicate whether to allow the driver user to allow controlling media sessions of a passenger user.

        This is per user setting and the drvier's Media Control Center app will query this to check whether it can connect/control other user's media session. The value type is boolean (1 for true, or 0 for false. false by default).
